quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  55,1,The Compassionate
  55,2,Hath taught the Qur'an
  55,3,He created man
  55,4,He taught distinctness
  55,5,The sun and the moon are in a reckoning
  55,6,And the herbs and the trees do obe isance
  55,7,"And the heaven! He hath elevated it, and He hath set the balance"
  55,8,That ye should not trespass in respect of the balance
  55,9,"And observe the weight with equity, and make not deficient the balance"
  55,10,And the earth! He hath lain it out for the creatures
  55,11,Therein are fruit and palm-trees sheathed
  55,12,And grain chaffed and other food
  55,13,"Which, then, of the benefits of your Lord, will ye twain belie"
  55,14,"He created man of clay like, Unto pottery"
  55,15,And He created the Jinn of a flame of fire
  55,16,"Which, then, of the benefits of your Lord will ye twain belie"
  55,17,He is Lord of the two easts and Lord of the two wests
  55,18,"Which, then, of the benefits of your Lord will ye twain belie"
  55,19,He hath let loose the two seas
  55,20,In-between the twain is a barrier which they pass not
  55,21,"Which, then, of the benefits of your Lord will ye twain belie"
  55,22,There come forth from the twain the pearl and the coral
  55,23,"Which, then, of the benefits of your Lord will ye twain belie"
  55,24,His are the ships with elevated sails upon the sea like mountains
  55,25,"Which, then, of the benefits of your Lord will ye twain belie"